    You should try the NWBStartup command from the NCS 1.80 which
return a pointer to the WBMessage (so you can get the lock) if the
program is started from the WB (else it return 0). Note that the
use of this function lock the Compiler V2.10.. I don't know why,
so test it trough your executable :-). On V1.7 it works so well...

