@NODE "Mail_273" "Re: Gadget sensibility"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 28 May 1999 11:04:52 +0100
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Fri, 28 May 1999 11:03:59 +0100
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: Gadget sensibility
Encoding: 7bit

Linda Bell wrote:

> Schnider Angel wrote,
> >I want to know which flag is used for detecting the if the mouse pointer is
> over a gadget.?
> >thanks..
>
> I don`t think there is one - $20 is for `gadget-down` and $40 is for
> `gadget-up`

I think there is, but only with later versions of the os.  A flag was added to
help with help systems so that when you press the help key over a gadget
context sensitive help was initiated and as a by product of this there is a
message to detect if you are over a gadget.  It'll be in the autodocs
somewhere...

    Thom


