Encoding: 7bit

On Sun, 02 May 1999 06:43:10 -0500 Curt Esser said:
> Hi Tony
> 
> On 02-May-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:
> > On Fri, 30 Apr 1999 21:49:57 +0100 Dave said:
> >> I think that when you active a new string gadget, it deactives the last
> >> one (I think so anyway), but your still left with a string gadget active.
> >> I was wondering if you could have a string gadget, say, invisible, not
> >> shown in the window, but in the gadget list, and activate that, and the
> >> current one would deactivate (probably doesn`t work..but maybe worth
> >> looking into??)
> > 
