> On 03-May-99, Paul Burkey wrote:
>  
> > there's no difference between a normal amiga bitmap and the bitmap
> > created by the OS. They are one and the same. You will find it hard
> > to create a planar bitmap with the OS if you`re running a CGFX system.
> > If you`re running CyberGFX then you can presume that all bitmaps will
> > probably be chunky and usually located in video ram. Just as you
> > can presume that without CyberGFX you'll probably get planar bitmaps
> > located in chip ram.
>  
>   I assume that CGFX under AGA, uses planar- unless it does or can do
> chunky bitmaps in fast, and C2Ps them.

It just depends what screenmode you choose. Some gfx cards can do
planar modes. mostly they are chunky so if you choose a chunky
screenmode then it will work in chunky. if you choose an aga mode it
will work in aga.

