>
>hmmm :) not so personal afterall ;)
>

I don`t rate mui much either...what it does is take a slimline fast os+gui
and add a lot of fancy stuff which I never use. Ok, so without it, there
probably wouldn`t have been amirc, or yam (which are the ONLY two reasons I
run that), but could they have been programmed without mui...yes, but would
they look so good...probably no, and I don`t think that it`s easier to
program mui...but it saves the programmer having to create his own special
mui type gadgets.


Dave <- Member of the `keep the amiga pure` group


