@NODE "Mail_479" "Re: MultiView (OFF TOPIC)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 16 May 1999 12:40:31 +0100
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
	"Luca Carminati" <toffi@spm.it>
Subject: Re: MultiView (OFF TOPIC)
Date: Sun, 16 May 1999 12:36:07 +0100

Luca wrote
>I wondered if there is a way to force documentations which has MultiView
>as default tool in the icon to open on a custom screen. I know that
>MultiView has the SCREEN tooltype, but I don't know how to set it when
>it's called from an icon.


SOLUTION A: Type "SCREEN" in tooltypes (that`s it).

SOLUTION B  Run multiview, check "USE SEPARATE SCREEN" from the menu, check
"SAVE AS DEFAULT" from the menu.

Don`t know if tooltypes lets you specify screen res with solution A, but it
should run in same res as WB - so you could try solution B, and see what the
icon info shows.

VIC




