@NODE "Mail_512" "Re: New Problem (Was: Icons and stuff)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 6 May 1999 11:58:43 +0000
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Thu, 06 May 1999 11:58:04 +0100
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: New Problem (Was: Icons and stuff)
Encoding: 7bit

David McMinn wrote:

> > 1) How do you use SortList?
>
> Then you'd do:
>
> SortList goat(),SizeOf.custom\number ; last part is field you want sort list on
>
> If you need to do string sorting in lists, then the is an RI lib for doing
> that, the commands are stringsort and stringsortdir.

In the help docs is says that SortList isn't fully implemented yet so it only works
on the first word of a type, even if the first two bytes are part of some larger
structure like a string, so if you wanted to sort a list of names it would only sort
by the first two letters.  If you need anything more than that you'll have to
implement your own sorting algorithm.

    Thom


