 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 5 May 1999 22:16:13 +0100
From: David McMinn <dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 05 May 1999 22:15:08 +0000
Organization: International House Of Mojo
Subject: Re: NewType problem (still causing many headaches, please help!)
Encoding: quoted-printable

steve@one3five.prestel.co.uk's head burst.
All we could scape off the wall was NewType problem (still causing many
headaches, please help!).

They're done with pointers and linked lists (Blitz2000 will have tutorial=
s on
these, for the pointy-deficient:). So you'd need to change your newtype t=
o be
something liek:

NEWTYPE.menu
  label.s
  *nextmenu.menu
END NEWTYPE

 This now also means that you need to create memory space for each new in=
stance
of a menu newtype variable as you go. And free it at the end.

Do you *really* need to use linked lists? There's plenty of people on the=
 list
able to give help on these if you want, but if you're new to the concept,=
 you
maybe want to use an array, like Rob showed you, and read up about linked=
 lists
(any programming site on the web, programming books in a library etc).



Chow f'now
