Hi James

On 22-Mar-99, James L Boyd wrote:
> Hi all, 
> 
> Sorry to repost this, but looks like no-one noticed it :)
> 
> Does anyone know how to read the RGB values from within
> a palette object, as opposed to using PalRGB, RGB, AGABlue,
> etc, which use the current screen's palette?

Use the RIGFX library commands:

PaletteInfo (palette#) ;first to tell it what palette is to be used

AGAPalRed (colour register#) for AGA palettes

or

PALRed (register#)  for ECS palettes

