Subject: Re: Pure


> Hmmm, piece of cake, eh?   ;)

Yeah, sure

> How would you be able to use any variables at all?  Since some other
> program could come along and change them before the first program was ev=
en
> done...

Functions are your friend. Local variables are your friend. Local variable=
s are 
created on the stack each time the code is run, so they would be created f=
or 
each time the function was run, on the calling program's stack.


