The only way would be to define a newtype containing All your
variables, getmain enough memory for it and use the addresses of the
variables as offsets from a register.  (At least that's how I did it
on other architectures).   The problem with Blitz is that, ven if you
did *Ptr = <<get memory for newtype>>,
I'm not convinced that the pointer is not actually defined in the
executable.

