I don't like the way Blitz handles the default type pointers, i.e. *blah.b=
 or 
*blah.w, but apart from that they are fine. Oh, and apart from struct blah=
 
**var ;)

> You would do something along the lines of a newtype that would contain a=
n
> ascii character, a pointer to the previous ascii character, and a pointe=
r
> to the next ascii character - where ascii characters would include TABs,
