Seriously? You'd end up with 5 bytes per character, and you'd constantly h=
ave 
to change your list on every keypress. I think what normally would happen =
is 
you allocate a block into which you would put your characters, then you ha=
ve a 
list of these blocks. I don't know if it would be one line per block, as y=
ou'd 
have to limit line length (ala Ted), probably just a bunch of characters, =
not 
specific to anything.

And the block couldn't be too big, because if you deleted something from t=
he 
start of a block, it would take ages to shift all the characters back one =
place.

 
