@NODE "Mail_718" "Re: Strange happenings"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 13 May 1999 10:30:49 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 13 May 1999 10:29:00 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Strange happenings

> Can any one explain why the gadget is vertically offset from the box? Bo=
th
> have a Top parameter equal to the variable BoxTop, but the gadget is 13 =
(I
> think?) pixels vertically lower than the box.
> 
> Is this always 13?   Is it dependent on the font?   On something else?

I see you have used the dreaded gime00 flag on your window. It causes the 
window borders to be rendered separate (or masked or something) so you can=
't 
corrupt them. This has the unfortunate effect of offsetting gtgadts. Try 
sticking in a GTGZZPosition On|Off somewhere in the code (manual doesn't s=
ay 
where) but probably before creating your gadgets.


