@NODE "Mail_720" "Re: Strange happenings"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 13 May 1999 18:35:32 +0100
From: "Linda Bell" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Strange happenings
Date: Thu, 13 May 1999 18:31:04 +0100

Hmmm  There seens to be some confusion here, so thought I`d clarify it, as
after reading the first mail, I tried it out.

If you print "A" at 10,10, and WPlot (white) at 10,10, "A" is further down
and right than the pixel.

If you use $400 in the flags for the window "GimmeZeroZero", the pixel
appears in the same place as the "A"

The origin for graphics is the top-left of the WHOLE window, the origin for
text/gadgets is inside the window.  Using GimmeZeroZero moves the origin for
graphics to the inside.

VIC




