@NODE "Mail_728" "Re: Tabs in Listviews?"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 31 May 1999 10:32:27 +0100
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 31 May 99 13:44:38 +1000
Subject: Re: Tabs in Listviews?
Encoding: 7bit

On Sun, 30 May 1999 17:43:13 +0200 Mike Delling said:
> 
> 
> Hello Blitzers!
> 
> A small problem again...
> 
> I want to display an unproportional Front in a Listview. So far so good, now
> my problem is, that I can not set up a Tabulator in this Listview and
> without one it looks very strange.
> What can I do or must I use MUI?
> 
I'm doing the same thing, except I'm using a Scroller rather than a
ListView.   I found ListViews too restrictive in terms of what you can
do to the lines to be displayed (colours etc.)   If you want to use a
Scroller instead, it's a lot more work, but you have complete control
over what you display on the lines (because you have to display them
yourself).

If you want any help, mail me privately (unless you think everyone
will be interested).

Cheers
.
-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

