@NODE "Mail_775" "Re: VisualPrefs problems"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 22 May 1999 00:53:53 +0100
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 21 May 1999 18:40:13 -0500
Subject: Re: VisualPrefs problems

Hi James

On 21-May-99, James L Boyd wrote:
> Curt Esser churned out *this* drivel:
> 
> Curt, I was looking at this :
> 
>>> Yes, you can use a dummy error trap also:
>>>> 
>>>> SetErr
>>>> EndSetErr
>>>> Free GTlist x
>>>> ClrErr
> 
> Shouldn't it be :
> 
> SetErr
>  Free GTlist x ; in between these, so it does this on an error...?
> EndSetErr
> ClrErr

No, because the error occurs when trying to free the GTlist.

Putting it inside the error trap would create an error trap endless loop or
maybe an instant guru or something because the error trap itself would be
creating another error so it would keep looping back to the error trap...

Yes, it would be a guru - the stack would overflow after a bit...


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



