Hello,

   Ok, after playing with this code ALL day, I finally figured probably the
best way to create a dragable window with the screens image in it,.. This
way it should work on GFX cards Curt :), and it dosn`t use any more mem
than the size of the window you use. (secondary [spare] rastport).
And it looks really nice :).. You can tell where it is because it`s get a
black box around the edges, but you should be able to drag it around..
though it does flicker a little cos the window is being closed and
reopened :) (But then so does Back-Clock :), so it probably does the same?)

Thanks to David McMinn for pointing out the dumbass mistake I made :)

BTW - I`ve commented it all in case anyone wants to use it :)

Cya!
